<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1558,1584]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
The sexual generation has not yet been described (see Remarks 2 below) and the two generations in the lifecycle were linked by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[468,599,1594,1620]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="15 - 20" refId="ref41243" refString="Abe, Y. (1991) Host race formation in the gall wasp Andricus mukaigawae. Entomologia experimentalis et applicata, 58 (1), 15 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1570 - 7458.1991. tb 01446. x" type="journal article" year="1991">Abe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,306,1630,1656]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[312,440,1630,1656]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="436 - 447" refId="ref41059" refString="Abe, Y. (1986) Taxonomic status of the Andricus mukaigawae complex and its speciation with geographical parthenogenesis (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Applied Entomology and Zoology, 21 (3), 436 - 447. https: // doi. org / 10.1303 / aez. 21.436" type="journal article" year="1986">Abe (1986)</bibRefCitation>
described the sexual form of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mukaigawa, 1913)" authorityName="Yasumatsu &amp; Masuda" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Mukaigawa" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[769,1244,1630,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaigawae">
<emphasis box="[769,1018,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Andricus mukaigawae</emphasis>
(Mukaigawa, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
from galls found on several 
<taxonomicName box="[275,465,1666,1693]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[275,369,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Quercus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Later, all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu &amp; Masuda" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Mukaigawa" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[582,756,1666,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaigawae">
<emphasis box="[582,756,1666,1693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. mukaigawae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
material obtained from 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1150,1666,1693]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis box="[1031,1150,1666,1693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Q. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to a new species named 
<taxonomicName authority="(Abe 1998)" baseAuthorityName="Abe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[319,645,1702,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashiwaphilus">
<emphasis box="[319,509,1702,1729]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. kashiwaphilus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[522,637,1702,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="131 - 135" refId="ref41446" refString="Abe, Y. (1998) Karyotype differences and speciation in the gall wasp Andricus mukaigawae (s. lat.) (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the new species A. kashiwaphilus. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 29 (2), 131 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631298 X 00249" type="journal article" year="1998">Abe 1998</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The characters used to differentiate both sexual forms (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu &amp; Masuda" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Mukaigawa" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1265,1437,1702,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaigawae">
<emphasis box="[1265,1437,1702,1729]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. mukaigawae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[183,374,1738,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashiwaphilus">
<emphasis box="[183,374,1738,1765]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. kashiwaphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are not mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[625,755,1738,1764]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="131 - 135" refId="ref41446" refString="Abe, Y. (1998) Karyotype differences and speciation in the gall wasp Andricus mukaigawae (s. lat.) (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the new species A. kashiwaphilus. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 29 (2), 131 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631298 X 00249" type="journal article" year="1998">Abe (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, and we assume that the sexual form of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[1201,1392,1738,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashiwaphilus">
<emphasis box="[1201,1392,1738,1765]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. kashiwaphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not yet been formally described.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,306,1810,1836]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks (3).</emphasis>
The asexual generations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[614,804,1810,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashiwaphilus">
<emphasis box="[614,804,1810,1837]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. kashiwaphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu &amp; Masuda" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Mukaigawa" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[857,1029,1810,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaigawae">
<emphasis box="[857,1029,1810,1837]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. mukaigawae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[1223,1352,1810,1836]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="131 - 135" refId="ref41446" refString="Abe, Y. (1998) Karyotype differences and speciation in the gall wasp Andricus mukaigawae (s. lat.) (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the new species A. kashiwaphilus. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 29 (2), 131 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631298 X 00249" type="journal article" year="1998">Abe (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, identical except for their karyotypes. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Tang, G. &amp; Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M." box="[626,937,1846,1873]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref51876" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Tang, G., Shen, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. (2016 b) Andricus mukaigawae and Andricus kashiwaphilus from China with remarks of morphological differences and inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Butlleti de la Institucio Catalana d'Historia Natural, 80, 17 - 24." type="journal article" year="2016">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[783,833,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. (2016b)
</bibRefCitation>
mentions some morphological characters to differentiate them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1450,2017]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1918,1944]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[302,570,1918,1944]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashiwaphilus">
<emphasis box="[302,570,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Andricus kashiwaphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
induces galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[765,883,1918,1945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis box="[765,883,1918,1945]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Q. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1051,1919,1945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1051,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), forming integral leaf galls in the sexual generation and large flower- or burr-shaped bud galls in the asexual generation (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[1237,1351,1954,1980]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="131 - 135" refId="ref41446" refString="Abe, Y. (1998) Karyotype differences and speciation in the gall wasp Andricus mukaigawae (s. lat.) (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the new species A. kashiwaphilus. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 29 (2), 131 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631298 X 00249" type="journal article" year="1998">Abe 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="169 - 212" refId="ref42072" refString="Abe, Y., Melika, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2007) The diversity and phylogeography of cynipid gallwasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) of the Oriental and Eastern Palearctic regions, and their associated communities. Oriental Insects, 41 (1), 169 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2007.10417504" type="journal article" year="2007">
Abe 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
